article.headline: Butler 91, MVSU 71
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS -- Matt Howard scored 26 points and Shelvin Mack added 12 as Butler beat Mississippi Valley State 91-71 on Saturday night. The Bulldogs (5-4), last year's national runner-up, avoided falling below .500 for the first time since they began the 2005-06 season with a 2/3 mark. Terrence Joyner and Kevin Burwell had 13 points each, and Jason Holmes had five blocks for the Delta Devils (1-6), which had not played since beating Georgia Southern on Nov. 27. After D'Angelo Jackson's 3-pointer gave it a 3-2 lead, Mississippi Valley State went scoreless for the next 7:23, enabling Butler to build a double-digit cushion it maintained for the rest of the game.
